#Text=The Golden State Warriors ( 66 - 15 ) defeated the Memphis Grizzlies ( 54 - 27 ) 111 - 107 on Monday at Oracle Arena in Oakland .
#Text=Already having locked up the number one overall seed in the Western Conference , the Warriors gained even more momentum against a very tough Grizzlies ' team .

#Text=The Warriors shot the ball extremely well , going 52 percent from the field and 54 percent from the three - point line , while the Grizzlies finished at 42 percent from the floor and 33 percent from deep .
#Text=This marks a tough loss for the Grizzlies , as they will likely be out of the running for the number two overall seed for the playoffs .

#Text=With that being said , they will move down to the sixth seed and fall a half game behind the San Atonio Spurs , Houston Rockets and Los Angeles Clippers , who all came up with victories on Monday .
#Text=The Warriors can thank Klay Thompson for this victory , as he was unstoppable all night long .
#Text=He went a ridiculous 15 - for - 21 from the field and 8 - for - 10 from the three - point line to score a game - high of 42 points , while also adding six rebounds and three assists as well .
#Text=If Thompson and Stephen Curry both get hot for the playoffs , this team will be very tough to beat .

#Text=Thompson is averaging 30 points over his last three games , while also hitting at least three three - pointers in each of those outings , so he 's well on his way to hitting his groove with the playoffs starting Saturday .
#Text=Curry , on the other hand , was the only other Warrior 's player to reach double figures in points .
#Text=He finished with 15 points and eight assists , while shooting 6 - for - 10 from the floor and 3 - for - 6 from deep .
#Text=Curry is shooting unbelievably well right now .
#Text=He 's finished over 50 percent from the field in each of his last five games , while shooting over 45 percent from the three - point line in those five games as well .
#Text=Arguably the current leader in the MVP race , Curry is averaging 24 points and 8 assists on the season , as he 'll look to take his hot shooting into the postseason .
#Text=Along with holding Mike Conley out of this game , the Grizzlies also limited the minutes of their starters , as Beno Udrih was the only starter to play over 22 minutes .
#Text=Because of that , it was the bench that did the majority of the work for the Grizzlies .
#Text=Rookie Jordan Adams came out of nowhere to score a career - high of 19 points ( 6 - 15 FG , 2 - 5 3Pt , 5 - 7 FT ) in 21 minutes off the bench .
#Text=He had only reach double - digit points in two other games this season and only averages 3 points per game , so it was a very nice surprise for this team .
#Text=Russ Smith also had a very surprising performance off the bench .
#Text=He went 5 - for - 8 from the field and 1 - for - 2 from the three - point line to score a season - high of 16 points .
#Text=He did it in only 10 minutes of action , which made it all the more impressive .
#Text=Zach Randolph was the only starter in double figures , as he posted 10 points ( 3 - 7 FG , 4 - 4 FT ) and five rebounds over 21 minutes .
#Text=The Warriors ' final game will be at home against the Denver Nuggets on Wednesday , while the Grizzlies will be at home against the Indiana Pacers on Wednesday .
